## Limitations

The primary limitation of this report is the evolving nature of research on transgender identity. As scientific understanding progresses, new findings may emerge that could alter current perspectives. Additionally, the complexity of gender identity means that individual experiences can vary widely, and not all aspects of transgender identity are fully understood or agreed upon within the scientific community.

